track_notes: 3.1 mile hike with 1300 EG.  Trailhead (34.783, -83.789) is at the junction of FS Road 44 and 44C.  FS 44 is now open from Unicoi Gap all the way to GA 75A.  The section from Unicoi Gap to the trailhead is a bit rougher and if your vehicle has limited clearance, I suggest approaching from the southern end.  Follow 44C 2.1 miles (660 EG) to the junction with the Appalachian Trail in Poplar Stamp Gap.  Turn right/North on the AT and then decide where to start your off-trail hike.  The further you hike on the AT, the further you will have to climb to regain the ridgeline.  There is a fair amount of brush and there is a band of briers part of the way up, but nothing was very dense (in January) and it was easy to negotiate around the worst parts.  Pretty densely forested hardwood summit but no problem finding a suitable spot for setup.
track_title: W4G/NG-009 Horsetrough Mountain via Poplar Stamp Gap

track_notes: 4.1 mile hike with 1800 foot EG and 800 foot EL.  Parking for ~10 vehicles at the turnoff for Brasstown Bald on Hwy 180 (34.847944, -83.798722).  Jacks Knob Trail starts across Hwy 180 and follow it 2.1 miles to the intersection with the AT in Chattahoochee Gap.  Follow the AT southbound 1.2 miles to Cold Springs Gap and then head off-trail up the ridgeline 0.9 miles to the summit.  The off-trail section starts with a steep section with a handful of blowdowns to navigate, but is less steep after that.  Lots of briers along this route so it is best activated during the winter months.
track_title: W4G/NG-009 - Horsetrough Mtn via Jacks Knob Trail
